headline: How Investors May Respond To CF (CF) CFO Transition And Low‑Carbon Ammonia Partnership Developments
summary: Earlier this month, CF Industries Holdings announced that Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer Gregory D. Cameron will leave the company on February 15, 2026, with long-time vice president, corporate controller and chief accounting officer Richard A. Hoker stepping in as interim CFO. At the same time, investors are watching CF Industries ahead of its expected fiscal Q4 2025 earnings release and its low-carbon ammonia collaboration with Trafigura and TFG Marine, which together...
